ZH: 我不抽烟，因为它会损害健康。
EN: I don't smoke because it damages health.

ZH: 他为了减压抽烟。
EN: He smokes to relieve stress.

ZH: 她被告知戒掉抽烟习惯。
EN: She was advised to quit smoking.

ZH: 我的父亲从不抽烟。
EN: My father never smokes.

ZH: 她喜欢在朋友聚会时抽烟。
EN: She enjoys smoking at social gatherings.

ZH: 他试图戒掉抽烟，但很难。
EN: He is trying to quit smoking but it's difficult.

ZH: 我每天只抽一两支烟。
EN: I only smoke one or two cigarettes per day.

ZH: 她抽烟多年后终于戒掉了。
EN: After many years of smoking, she finally quit.

ZH: 我这个星期想暂时戒烟。
EN: I want to temporarily quit smoking this week.

ZH: 我朋友已经抽烟十年了。
EN: My friend has been smoking for ten years.

ZH: 抽烟会让你的皮肤显得暗淡无光。
EN: Smoking makes your skin look dull.

ZH: 我的爷爷曾经是个抽烟的厨师。
EN: My grandfather used to be a smoking chef.

ZH: 抽烟影响人的味觉和嗅觉。
EN: Smoking affects a person's sense of taste and smell.

ZH: 我决定戒掉抽烟来改善健康状况。
EN: I decided to quit smoking to improve my health.

ZH: 我试过用口香糖来戒掉抽烟。
EN: I tried using chewing gum to quit smoking.

ZH: 他在抽烟后感到非常愧疚。
EN: He feels very guilty after smoking.

ZH: 抽烟会导致许多严重的健康问题。
EN: Smoking can lead to many serious health issues.

ZH: 我在一年前停止抽烟了。
EN: I quit smoking a year ago.

ZH: 吸二手烟和自己抽烟一样危险。
EN: Secondhand smoke is as dangerous as smoking itself.

ZH: 我要坚持不再抽烟。
EN: I will persist in not smoking anymore.
